      "content": "that makes sense. so if i'm arguing the humanitarian side, i can basically treat the border security side as just a legal technicality that doesn't really hold up morally? like, since you said protecting people is a \"non-negotiable good,\" does that mean the people arguing for strict border enforcement are basically choosing policy over human lives?",
